[src:generating-functions/binomial-coefficient] The proof is similar, but uses the binomial series expansion (**2**) with negative integer exponents.
[src:generating-functions/binomial-coefficient] Let *F*(*n*) denote the *n*-th Fibonacci number.
[src:generating-functions/binomial-coefficient] Then $\sum _{k=0}^{\lfloor n/2\rfloor }{\binom {n-k}{k}}=F(n+1).$ This can be proved by induction using (**3**) or by Zeckendorf's representation.
