[src:generating-functions/exponential-generating-function-p01] Examples of P-recursive sequences with holonomic generating functions include *f**n* ≔ ⁠1/*n* + 1⁠ (2*n* *n*) and *f**n* ≔ ⁠2*n*/*n*2 + 1⁠, where sequences such as ${\sqrt {n}}$ and log *n* are *not* P-recursive due to the nature of singularities in their corresponding generating functions.
[src:generating-functions/exponential-generating-function-p01] Similarly, functions with infinitely many singularities such as tan *z*, sec *z*, and Γ(*z*) are *not* holonomic functions.
[src:generating-functions/exponential-generating-function-p01] Tools for processing and working with P-recursive sequences in *Mathematica* include the software packages provided for non-commercial use on the RISC Combinatorics Group algorithmic combinatorics software site.
