[src:generating-functions/formal-power-series] Formal power series can be used to solve recurrences occurring in number theory and combinatorics.
[src:generating-functions/formal-power-series] For an example involving finding a closed form expression for the Fibonacci numbers, see the article on Examples of generating functions.
[src:generating-functions/formal-power-series] One can use formal power series to prove several relations familiar from analysis in a purely algebraic setting.
[src:generating-functions/formal-power-series] For *K* a field, the ring $K[[X_{1},\ldots ,X_{r}]]$ is often used as the "standard, most general" complete local ring over *K* in algebra.
[src:generating-functions/formal-power-series] In mathematical analysis, every convergent power series defines a function with values in the real or complex numbers.
[src:generating-functions/formal-power-series] Formal power series over certain special rings can also be interpreted as functions, but one has to be careful with the domain and codomain.
