[src:generating-functions/stirling-numbers-of-the-second-kind] The parity of a central Stirling number of the second kind $\textstyle \left\{{2n \atop n}\right\}$ is odd if and only if n is a fibbinary number, a number whose binary representation has no two consecutive 1s.
